replies.bodyText:
My point is not about what enum names to use.
Adding getLanguage to SqlFunction leaves a hole in the API. User will be allowed to define a SQL-invoked function (either through CREATE FUNCTION statement, or through plugin) with language Java. Similarly, SqlScalarFunction instance can have language SQL. In both cases, functions can be created but fails with internal error during execution.
Example:
CREATE FUNCTION dev.leiqing.rand()
RETURNS double
LANGUAGE JAVA
RETURN rand()
It will succeeds, but execution will fail. We shouldn't allow the create function to work in the first place.
Similarly, one can also do:
public class XXXFunction extends SqlScalarFunction {
   @Override
   public Language getLanguage() {
       return SQL;
    }
}
Although this is clearly wrong and can be easily caught by test, but why test? We shouldn't allow it structurally in the first place.
Hopefully, this examples explain my concerns.
